INFLUSCIENCE: Cientfic@s socialmente influyentes: Un modelo para medir la transferencia del conocimiento en la sociedad digital

  • Funder: Ministerio de Ciencia e Innovacin, Plan Nacional de I+D+i

  • Budget: 60,500

  • Funder: TU Delft COVID-19 Response Fund

  • Period: 2020-2021
  • Budget: 20,000
  • Project summary

ECOSCI: Unveiling the Ecosystem of Science: A Contextual Perspective into the Many Roles of Scientists

  • Funder: European Commission, COFUND Marie Curie Fellowship, LEaDing Fellows programme
  • Role: PI (with supervisor Gabriela F. Nane)
  • Partners: TU Delft and Leiden University
  • Period: 2019-2021
  • Budget: 220,000
  • Project summary

Connecting nuances of foreign status, professional networks and higher education

  • Funder: US National Science Foundation
  • Role: Postdoctoral researcher (with PI Eric W. Welch and Co-PI Julia Melkers)
  • Partners: Arizona State University, Georgia Institute of Technology and University of Arkansas
  • Period: 2017-2019
  • Budget: $1,100,000
  • Outputs: Conference paper Conference paper Working paper

Visiting Scholar Henk F. Moed Disentangling Gold Open Access

  • Funder: University of Granada. Plan Propio de Investigacin y Transferencia. Programa Visiting Scholars
  • Role: Core scientific team (with PI Daniel Torres-Salinas)
  • Partners: University of Granada and Universitat Politcnica de Valncia)
  • Period: 2017
  • Budget: 10,000
  • Outputs: Book chapter Conference paper
